source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cheddar-stuffed-meatloaves-63c81980cd3595c98c0a41e9
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ¼-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}.

Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. (Save potatoes for another use.)

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{} (for 4 servings, spread out across entire sheet).

Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

In a #large bowl{}, toss Brussels sprouts with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} (you'll start roasting in Step 4).

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, soak @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup} with @water{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and @beef stock concentrate{1} until liquid has absorbed. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, @salt{½%tsp} (1 tsp for 4), and @pepper{}; mix to combine.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160º.

Form beef mixture into two ½-inch-thick rounds (four rounds for 4). Reserve half the @cheddar cheese{½%cup} for topping; divide remaining cheddar between the centers of each round. Gently fold meat around cheese, shaping and sealing to create 1-inch-thick loaves.

Once potatoes have roasted ~{5%minutes}, remove baking sheet from oven. Add meatloaves to opposite side of sheet. (For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting; add meatloaves to a second baking sheet and roast on middle rack.)

Roast on top rack until potatoes are browned and tender and meatloaves are cooked through, ~{17-20%minutes} more.

In the last ~{2%minutes} of roasting, top meatloaves with reserved cheddar. Return to oven until cheese melts.

Place Brussels sprouts and meatloaves on opposite sides of a baking sheet; roast on top rack, ~{15-20%minutes}. Cook through the rest of this step as instructed.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large, heavy-bottomed pan{} over medium-high heat. Add carrots and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> If carrots begin to brown too quickly, add a few splashes of water.

Turn off heat; transfer carrots to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

In a #small bowl{}, toss shallot with @flour{1%tablespoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In #pan{} used for carrots, heat a 1/3-inch layer of @cooking oil{} over medium heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of flour sizzles immediately when added to the pan, add coated shallot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer shallot to a paper-towel-lined plate.

Meanwhile, in a separate small bowl, combine @ketchup{1} and @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}. Stir in @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice meatloaves crosswise if desired.

Divide meatloaves, potato wedges, and carrots between plates. Drizzle meatloaves with some of the special sauce. Serve remaining sauce on the side with potatoes for dipping. Garnish meatloaves with crispy shallot and serve.